# Group Comments
To add file attachments to a record, upload your files send a `POST` request with `Content-Type: multipart/form-data` to `https://cloud.zeyos.com/upload`, one file at a time.

You will receive a JSON-encoded object that looks like this for each uploaded file:

```json
{
    "name": "logo.png",
    "type": "image/png",
    "size": 15302,
    "tempfile": "zeyosk2x5jv"
}
```

Once all your attachments have been uploaded, send your `PUT` or `POST` to create or update your `comments` object and supply a sub-array `files` of all objects you received before.

The uploads will then be linked to the record, and the associated upload objects will be invalidated upon successful return and cannot be used any more.

Upload objects will also expire automatically a day after creation.


